      {
        "id": "63b0aa9a23f2efe421f3f82e2f8411a389c278d8",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3237,
          "name": "Waqas Ikram",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "waqas.ikram@est.tech",
          "username": "waqas.ikram"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-09-23 10:55:39.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nBy default the tomcat will unpack the content of the WAR file (See https://www.oreilly.com/library/view/tomcat-the-definitive/9780596101060/ch03s04.html), in that case logback.xml can be change at runtime. But i still think, the logback shouldn't be part of the WAR, as on deploying new war will overrride the previous logback settings/file and plus the logging approach should be consistence as other applications in SO.\n\nSuggested better solution to the guys in the call to test, which will allow us to move logback out of the WAR file.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "24f9851a2414d9a5ff31ee0720118461009fd54b",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 897,
          "name": "Seshu Kumar Mudiganti",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "seshukumar.mudiganti@windriver.com",
          "username": "seshukm"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-09-24 04:59:25.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> By default the tomcat will unpack the content of the WAR file (See https://www.oreilly.com/library/view/tomcat-the-definitive/9780596101060/ch03s04.html), in that case logback.xml can be change at runtime. But i still think, the logback shouldn't be part of the WAR, as on deploying new war will overrride the previous logback settings/file and plus the logging approach should be consistence as other applications in SO.\n> \n> Suggested better solution to the guys in the call to test, which will allow us to move logback out of the WAR file.\n\nI understand the concern you raised here waqas, but unlike the other so pods bpmn infra will be a tomcat application while others are springboot\nThere are options to change the logging of webapps in tomcat, that we can check further.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
